    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The degree of well-being felt by an individual about his or her lifestyle, often defined in terms of social indicators, such as nutrition, air quality, crime rates, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046397/Oxford Companion to Philosophy (1995)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046351/Dictionary of Geography (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>El grado de sentimiento de bienestar de un individuo por su estilo de vida, a menudo definido en los términos de indicadores sociales, como nutrición, calidad del aire, tasa de criminalidad, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De mate van welzijn die een persoon ervaart met betrekking tot zijn manier van leven, vaak gedefinieerd in termen van sociale indicatoren, zoals voeding, luchtkwaliteit, criminaliteitscijfers, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
